    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Repair the HIGH-tier Email association tests under
    `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Email/EmailAssociation*` (~863 LOC). Per design.md §3.3
    these are HIGH-tier (pure algorithm; matter association is load-bearing for email→matter routing).

    COORDINATION NOTE: Per design.md §2.3 and project CLAUDE.md, the `x-email-communication-solution-r2`
    project owner must be aware of any test edits in `Services/Email/*` and `Services/Communication/*`.
    Before significant edits, post a note in the daily sync channel; align on whether the production
    Email association code is expected to change in r2.

    For each failing test:
    1. Identify failure (matcher rule change, scoring change, fallback behavior change)
    2. Determine: `test-stale` (update assertion) vs `production-bug` (mark `real-bug-pending-fix` + ledger)
    3. Apply §6.2 trait
    4. Verify Pass

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02 + design.md §4.1: this is repair, NOT rewrite. If ANY file's diff
    would exceed 50% line replacement, HALT and file
    `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-043-{FileName}.md`
    per §4.8 escalation procedure. Do NOT proceed without owner approval.

    NO production code changes (NFR-01). Per §6.2, every touched test ends in `repaired`,
    `real-bug-pending-fix`, `flaky-quarantined`, or archived. `Failed` is FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET test repair specialist with email-to-matter association domain knowledge.</role>

  <goal>
    All Email association test files end in §6.2 final end-state. Zero Failed. Coordination outcome
    with x-email-communication-solution-r2 owner recorded.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
